iCBT is Internet-based Cognitive Behaviour Therapy (CBT). CBT is the most effective and commonly used therapy for a wide range of mental health concerns. iCBT by Morneau Shepell brings you a personalized therapist-guided program that can help improve your life by changing the way you think, feel, and behave through developing new skills and strategies.
A therapist will be with you from beginning to end. They\'ll guide you through articles, videos, and exercises. All this from the comfort of your living room.
Working with experts, the articles and videos were tailored to help you. You\'ll be able to learn, confront and overcome your concerns.
Each module has multiple exercises. As you complete an exercise it\'s sent to your therapist. They\'ll review your progress and provide valuable tips and feedback.

You can chat anytime with your therapist through messages. If you have questions or thoughts, you\'ll be able to send them a message. Your therapist will reply and also reach out to you with helpful advice or tips.

One of the most common sleep disorders is Insomnia. If falling asleep or sleeping through the night is difficult, you might have insomnia.
Due to stress at work or at home, many people have experienced insomnia at some point. When you experience lack of sleep for long periods of time, this can impact your quality of life. You may develop emotional problems, irritability, anxiety or cognitive difficulties.
We designed our insomnia program using cognitive behavioural therapy (CBT). You\'ll identify what thoughts and behaviours negatively impact your sleep patterns. Arm with this knowledge, you can replace them with better patterns to improve your sleep. Learn to deal with the problems impacting your sleep instead of using medication.
Working with your therapist, you\'ll improve your sleep quality over the long-term.

Feeling anxious is normal from time to time. If you find yourself in a constant place of worry and fear, then anxiety has taken control on your life. Anxiety presents the following emotional and physical symptoms.

Cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT) can help with you with anxiety. You will learn to identify negative thought patterns and replace them with more realistic and positive ones. You will also learn to identify the physical symptoms and feelings when you’re anxious. Finally you will learn the skills needed to cope with anxiety.

Are you having sad and experiencing hoplessness? Do you have trouble sleeping, notice a loss of energy and interest in daily activities? Feeling sad can be a normal part of the ups and downs of life. When the feelings of helplessness, emptiness and worthlessness take hold of your life, you may be have depression.
Depression can impact your daily life for you and the people who care about you. It becomes difficult to function and enjoy life. Sleeping, working, eating and social outings are difficult to manage. It can feel like you\'re no longer in control of your life.
Using cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT) can be an effective way to treat depression. Working with this program, you\'ll learn not to let negative thoughts influence your reality. Instead you\'re learn to replace these thoughts with a healthier way of thinking. CBT will teach you coping methods to face life without feeling anxious or depressed.
By the time you\'re done, you\'ll feel better about yourself - both in the present and the future.
* Two additional payments of $75.00 will be required as you work through the program.

Everyone feels pain from time to time. When you pull a muscle or get a headache, pain is your body\'s way to telling you there\'s a problem. Once you heal, the pain stops. Chronic pain is different. You can feel pain for weeks, months or even years after the injury.
Chronic pain can vary from mild to severe. It can be a daily problem or it can come and again. Pain is displayed with many symptoms:

Cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT) is successfully used to treat chronic pain. You\'ll learn to function with the pain without the pain deceasing. You\'ll learn to accept your situation and learn how to live with it. You\'ll discover that that believing improvement is possible is a key factor of the healing power of your mind.
This program teaches the concepts needed to manage your pain and stop living in fear of it.
